title: Tech in position through 36 holes at ACC Championship - VT hokiesports.com
content: Tech in position through 36 holes at ACC Championship  VT hokiesports.com
description: Virginia Tech is tied for fourth place with North Carolina State after day one of the ACC Women's Golf Championship. The Reserve Golf Club is the host course of the tournament and is a par 72 that measures out to 6,212 yards. The Hokies wrapped up day one shooting a combined 296 and 289, positioning themselves at 9-over-par.
